'''ABC Northern Tasmania''' (call sign: '''7NT''') is the [[ABC Local Radio]] station for northern [[Tasmania]], based in [[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]], owned by the [[Australian Broadcasting Corporation]]. It broadcasts on 91.7&nbsp;MHz on the FM band.

==History==
ABC Northern Tasmania was the ABC radioâs first regional station in Launceston. It was opened by [[Prime Minister]] [[Joseph Lyons]] on 3 August 1935.

7NT moved from AM (711&nbsp;kHz) to FM (91.7&nbsp;MHz) in 2006.

